* :9jfGaOnx9TjViX8W: a design pattern which provides a way to write concurrent, parallel and distributed programs by message passing. Compared to the use of threads and locks, this is a high level programming model using communication constructs model to abstract the complexity of concurrent environment and to allow scalability. Its focus is on the execution of a chord between messages atomically consumed from a group of channels
